This is the report of my research involving 3 CD's:

Marilyn Manson-Mechanical Animals which contains a Skeleton(Henger/???)
Guns N' Roses-Appetite for Destruction which also contains a Skeleton(Henger/???)
Guns N' Roses-Appetite for Destruction which contains a Citronie(Kato/Suezo)

The test was made comparing the results of the three CD's in Monster Rancher
1, Monster Rancher 2 and Monster Rancher Battle Cards Episode II.

Unfortunately I don't own a CD Copier so I won't be able to compare the
number of frames of each CD. Anyway some of you might be interested in it.

I will post in parts so I won't have to write it all at once.

I will also post it in other Monster Rancher related sites.

If I put my hands in a CD copier I will for sure add more information to this thread.

Skeleton X Skeleton>>>>>>>>>>

Conclusions:
1-The CD's are very different both in duration and number of tracks, anyway they have the same monster.
2-The Skeletons are NOT equal, CD1's stats are higher and it has an additional hit tech: arm cannon.


Roses X Roses>>>>>>>>>>

Conclusions:
1-The CD's have the same the same UPC's but CD2 was pressed in 1999 by Microservice Tecnologia Digital da Amazônia and CD3 in 1991 by Sonopress- Rimo da Amazônia Industrial e Comércio Fonográfica LTDA.
2-In Monster Rancher1 they have the same monster, with the same set of stats.
3-In Monster Rancher 2 they have VERY different monsters, and in MRCBEp.II they have different cards.
4-CD3 is 2seconds shorter than CD2, the difference comes from the last track(Rocket Queen)

Final Conclusions>>>>>>>>>>

1-MR and MR2 shrines probably take different things into consideration to generate monsters, because CD2 and CD3 have identical monsters in MR1 but different ones in MR2.
2-I believe I'm giving enough proof that two CD's with same UPC's are not necessarily with the same monster as everyone thought.
3-I did it in a hurry, if I forgot to mention anything please tell me. Any question, just ask.
